choices.text:
not the sound of kids. My biggest problem is the droning of a big diesel truck or a noisy generator.

The problems go from bad to worse, so the machines need two fuel pumps. So there’s two engines running at all times. Once the solar panels charges the batteries, but not in the afternoons which rely on heavy generators for power.

And this roaring sound goes on all the time. Just gorgeous. And what do the Nauruans do, but to super-size the inside of own houses. In almost every custom built house the large members of the family need an air-conditioned room in addition to their bedroom. It can be a kitchen, a dining room or a living room. It’s just huge. And as of this past month the members of the government passed a law that the air-conditioned room has to be in the mainland. To do otherwise will make you run afoul of your permit to build a house.

So… when the jet noise, the droning of generators, and the kids yelling is done, is the honking of car horns when the car stops at traffic light, and goes on after the light turns green.

Now, you cannot yell at the fish or the birds to keep it down. They are babies and childrenesque. But you do yell at the exhaust from the car meant to go anywhere but here, and with climate change the natives will only get hotter, maybe even moving.

Dave
